Detailed Description

The reply to a RouteStorageGetRouteRequestPacket.

After the normal RequestPacket header the request packet contains: {tabular}{lll} Pos & Size & Destription \ REPLY_HEADER_SIZE & 4 bytes & RouteID \ +4 & 4 bytes & UIN \ +8 & 4 bytes & validUntil \ +12 & 4 bytes & createTime \ +18 & 4 bytes & routePack->getLength \ +16 & 2 bytes & strlen extraUserinfo \ +20 & extraUserinfo bytes & extraUserinfo \ & routePack bytes & routePack \ {tabular}

routePack The route stored, or NULL if none found.
UIN The user of the route, or 0 if none found.
extraUserinfo Extra information about the user, or empty string if none found.
validUntil Time when route can be considered "old" in UTC.
createTime The time, in UTC, when the route was created. Used to determine if the route contains current mc2-maps.
originLat The latitude of the route's origin.
